<doc id="616477" wikidata="Q929368" url="?curid=616477" title="Alper">
<text>Alper is a male Turkish given name. It is composed of the two words &quot;alp&quot; and &quot;er&quot;. In Turkish, &quot;Alp&quot; means &quot;Stouthearted&quot;, &quot;Brave&quot;, &quot;Chivalrous&quot;, &quot;Daredevil&quot;, and/or &quot;Valorous&quot;. The second, &quot;er&quot; means soldier or male. Additionally &quot;Alper&quot; is used as an adjective for an ancient legendary Turkish commander; Alp Er Tunga who lived around 300 B.C.
It&#x27;s meant to be a good hearted one too.
From the same Asian cultural roots, Alper is closely related to the name 勇士 (Japanese &quot;yuushi&quot;, Chinese &quot;yǒngshì&quot;) derived 勇 =Alp and 士 =Er words.

